    "*": "<tr>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-lineno\">Line 104:</td>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-lineno\">Line 104:</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\">&#160;</td>\n  <td class=\"diff-context\"></td>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\">&#160;</td>\n  <td class=\"diff-context\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\">&#160;</td>\n  <td class=\"diff-context\"><div>===Judaism===</div></td>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\">&#160;</td>\n  <td class=\"diff-context\"><div>===Judaism===</div></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\">−</td>\n  <td class=\"diff-deletedline\"><div><del class=\"diffchange diffchange-inline\">In the [[Hebrew Bible]], wisdom is represented by [[Solomon]], who asks God for wisdom in </del>{{<del class=\"diffchange diffchange-inline\">bibleref|2Chronicles|1}}. Much of the [[Book of Proverbs]], a book of wise sayings, is attributed to Solomon. In {{bibleref|Proverbs|1:7}} and {{bibleref|Proverbs|9:10}}, the awe of [[YHWH]] is called the beginning or foundation of wisdom while {{bibleref|Proverbs|8:13}} declares \"To fear YHWH is to hate injustice\". In {{bibleref|Proverbs|1:20}}, there is</del> also<del class=\"diffchange diffchange-inline\"> reference to wisdom personified in female form, \"Wisdom calls aloud in the streets, she raises her voice in the marketplaces.\" [[Adhan#Text</del>|<del class=\"diffchange diffchange-inline\">(Adan)]] Continuing in {{bibleref|Proverbs|8:22–31</del>}}<del class=\"diffchange diffchange-inline\">, this personified wisdom is described as being present with God before creation began and even taking part in creation itself, delighting especially in human beings.</del></div></td>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\">+</td>\n  <td class=\"diff-addedline\"><div>{{<ins class=\"diffchange diffchange-inline\">See</ins> also|<ins class=\"diffchange diffchange-inline\">Chokhmah</ins>}}</div></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"diff-empty\">&#160;</td>\n  <td class=\"diff-marker\">+</td>\n  <td clas